The paper deals with the application of evolutionary robotics techniques to obtain self-organized behaviors for robot swarms. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of neural network-based controllers, which is a common technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI, cs.NE). The paper also mentions the properties of swarm intelligence-based control, which is a subfield of multi-agent systems (cs.MA, cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO, followed by cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
